24
1 (c) If a legislative member of the commission ceases to be a
2 member of the legislative chamber from which the member was
3 appointed, the member ceases to be a member of the commission.
4 (d) A member of the commission:
5 (1) serves at the pleasure of the member's appointing
6 authority; and
7 (2) may be removed at any time by the appointing authority.
