15 drafting of the proposed minimum standards. County sheriffs shall be
16 selected from the various classes of counties to ensure that densely,
17 moderately, and sparsely populated counties are represented. Each
18 county sheriff is entitled to the minimum salary per diem as provided
19 in IC 4-10-11-2.1 for each day engaged in the official business of the
20 committee and to reimbursement for traveling and other expenses, as
21 provided in the state travel policies and procedures established by the
22 Indiana department of administration and approved by the budget
23 agency.
24 (d) At least sixty (60) days before setting the date for a public
25 hearing under IC 4-22-2, the department shall forward copies of the
26 proposed minimum standards to each county sheriff and each board of
27 county commissioners and shall solicit their views and suggestions.
