40 (1) The creation of a structure for a statewide 211 resources data
41 base.
42 (2) The development and implementation of a statewide 211
EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

69
1 resources data base described in subdivision (1). Permissible
2 expenditures under this subdivision include expenditures for
3 planning, training, accreditation, and system evaluation.
4 (3) Collecting, organizing, and maintaining information from state
5 agencies, departments, and programs that provide human
6 services, for access by a provider of 211 services.
7 (4) Providing grants for any of the following purposes to a
8 provider of 211 services:
9 (A) The design, development, and implementation of 211
10 services in the provider's 211 service area. Funds provided
11 under this clause may be used for planning, public awareness,
12 training, accreditation, and evaluation.
13 (B) The provision of 211 services on an ongoing basis after the
14 design, development, and implementation of 211 services in
15 the provider's service area.
16 (C) The provision of 211 services on a twenty-four (24) hour
17 per day, seven (7) day per week basis.
18 (e) The expenses of administering the fund shall be paid from
19 money in the fund.
20 (f) The treasurer of state shall invest the money in the fund not
21 currently needed to meet the obligations of the fund in the same
22 manner as other public money may be invested.
23 (g) Money in the fund at the end of a state fiscal year does not revert
24 to the state general fund.
