20 promulgated under this chapter shall prescribe the use of labels or other
21 appropriate forms of warning as are necessary to insure that employees
22 are apprised of all hazards to which they are exposed, relevant
23 symptoms and appropriate emergency treatment, and proper conditions
24 and precautions of safe use or exposure. Where appropriate, such a
25 standard shall also prescribe suitable protective equipment and control
26 or technological procedures to be used in connection with the hazards
27 and shall provide for monitoring or measuring employee exposure at
28 such locations and intervals and in such manner as may be necessary
29 for the protection of employees. In addition where appropriate, any
30 standard shall prescribe the type or frequency of medical examinations
31 or other tests which shall be made available by the employer, at
32 employer's cost, to employees exposed to hazards in order to most
33 effectively determine whether the health of the employees is adversely
34 affected by the exposure. Upon request, the results of examinations or
35 tests shall be furnished to the department and shall remain confidential
36 within the department. At the request of the employee, results shall be
37 furnished to his physician.
