7 (2) A refusal to make reasonable accommodations in rules,
8 policies, practices, or services, when the accommodations may be
9 necessary to afford the person equal opportunity to use and enjoy
10 a dwelling.
11 (3) In connection with the design and construction of covered
12 multifamily dwellings for first occupancy after March 13, 1991,
13 a failure to design and construct those dwellings in a manner that:
14 (A) the public use and common use parts of the dwellings are
15 readily accessible to and usable by persons with disabilities;
16 (B) all the doors are designed to allow passage into and within
17 all premises within the dwellings and are sufficiently wide to
18 allow passage by persons with disabilities in wheelchairs; and
19 (C) all premises within the dwellings contain the following
20 features of adaptive design:
21 (i) An accessible route into and through the dwelling.
22 (ii) Light switches, electrical outlets, thermostats, and other
23 environmental controls in accessible locations.
24 (iii) Reinforcements in bathroom walls to allow later
25 installation of grab bars.
26 (iv) Usable kitchens and bathrooms so that an individual in
27 a wheelchair can maneuver about the space.
