12 SECTION 282. IC 22-12-2 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY 1,
13 2027]. (Fire Prevention and Building Safety Commission).
14 SECTION 283. IC 22-12-2.1 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
15 CODE AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS
16 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2027]:
17 Chapter 2.1. Transition of Responsibilities for Fire Prevention
18 and Building Safety
19 Sec. 1. (a) On July 1, 2027, all powers, duties, agreements, and
20 liabilities of the fire prevention and building safety commission are
21 transferred to the department.
22 (b) On July 1, 2027, all records and property of the fire
23 prevention and building safety commission, including
24 appropriations and other funds under the control or supervision of
25 the fire prevention and building safety commission, are transferred
26 to the department.
27 (c) After June 30, 2027, any amounts owed to the fire prevention
28 and building safety commission before July 1, 2026, are considered
29 to be owed to the department as the successor agency.
30 (d) After June 30, 2027, a reference to the fire prevention and
31 building safety commission in a statute, rule, or other document is
32 considered a reference to the department.
33 (e) Proceedings pending before the fire prevention and building
34 safety commission on July 1, 2027, shall be transferred from the
35 fire prevention and building safety commission to the department
36 and treated as if initiated by the department.
37 (f) A license or permit issued by the fire prevention and building
38 safety commission before July 1, 2027, shall be treated after June
39 30, 2027, as a certification issued by the department.
40 (g) The rules adopted by the fire prevention and building safety
41 commission before July 1, 2027, are considered, after June 30,
42 2027, rules of the department. For purposes of applying IC 4-22-2.6
EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

152
1 to the readoption of rules transferred by this subsection, the rules
2 shall be treated as not expiring. Except as permitted under
3 IC 4-22-2-38 to make nonsubstantive technical corrections, the
4 department may not revise or repeal the transferred rules,
5 including matters incorporated by reference, unless authorized by
6 act of the general assembly.
7 (h) Not later than July 1, 2028, and each year thereafter, the
8 department shall submit a report to the legislative council in an
9 electronic format under IC 5-14-6 making recommendations for
10 amendment of the rules of the fire prevention and building safety
11 commission transferred to the department under this section. The
12 legislative council shall assign the report to be reviewed by an
13 interim study committee established under IC 2-5-1.3. In preparing
14 the report required by this subsection, the department shall consult
15 with industry experts, professionals, and interested stakeholders
16 who have indicated an interest in the subject matter of the
17 recommendations contained in the report.
