4 SECTION 342. IC 22-15-3.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
5 CODE AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS
6 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2027]:
7 Chapter 3.5. Self-certification by Design Professional
8 Sec. 1. The definitions in IC 22-15-3.2 apply throughout this
9 chapter.
10 Sec. 2. (a) Notwithstanding any other law, an applicant for a
11 construction project requiring a design release for a Class 1
12 structure under IC 22-15-3 may satisfy the design release
13 requirement through self-certification.
14 (b) Self-certification may be used only for projects that are
15 required to be signed and sealed by an Indiana registered design
16 professional. The department may exclude projects from
17 self-certification that involve high-hazard occupancies, essential
18 facilities, or other structures determined to pose an elevated risk
19 to life safety.
20 Sec. 3. To self-certify a project, an applicant for a design release
21 must:
22 (1) be an Indiana registered design professional in good
23 standing with the applicable registration board;
24 (2) be a registered design professional for at least two (2)
25 years;
26 (3) have completed at least five (5) projects in Indiana as the
27 registered design professional of record or as the registered
28 design professional responsible for the production of the
29 construction documents; and
30 (4) maintain professional liability insurance of at least five
31 hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) per claim and one
32 million dollars ($1,000,000) aggregate.
33 Sec. 4. The department shall develop an electronic application
34 form for self-certifying applicants.
35 Sec. 5. The certifying design professional shall:
36 (1) perform a comprehensive review of the construction
37 documents; and
38 (2) submit to the department a signed certification, under
39 penalty of perjury, affirming that the plans comply with all
40 applicable state building codes and rules.
41 Sec. 6. Upon receipt of a complete certification and required
42 documentation, the department shall, not later than the next
EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

181
1 business day, provide to the applicant:
2 (1) a copy of the design release; or
3 (2) a confirmation number that serves as a temporary design
4 release until the applicant receives a copy of the design
5 release;
6 without conducting a technical plan review.
7 Sec. 7. The department may:
8 (1) audit self-certified projects;
9 (2) require corrective action for noncompliance;
10 (3) revoke or suspend a professional's authority to provide
11 certifications; and
12 (4) refer violations to the appropriate licensing board or
13 impose civil penalties as authorized by law.
14 Sec. 8. The department may collect plan review fees for projects
15 that are released without a plan review.
16 Sec. 9. Nothing in this chapter limits the authority of state or
17 local inspection officials to conduct inspections or enforce
18 compliance during construction.
19 Sec. 10. An applicant who is qualified to self-certify may apply
20 for a design release under:
21 (1) this chapter; or
22 (2) IC 22-15-3.
23 Sec. 11. Participation in the self-certification program is
24 voluntary. Nothing in this chapter prohibits the department from
25 reviewing or not reviewing an application in accordance with
26 IC 22-15-3.
