19 within the entire project, or who fabricates elevator lifting devices
20 substantially completed and ready for installation.
21 (4) "Elevator inspector" means an individual who conducts the
22 acceptance inspection of a regulated lifting device required by
23 section 4(c)(1)(A) of this chapter.
24 (5) "Elevator mechanic" means an individual who engages in the
25 construction, reconstruction, alteration, maintenance, mechanical,
26 or electrical work or adjustments of a regulated lifting device.
27 (6) "License" means a certificate issued by the department that
28 confers upon the holder the privilege to act as an elevator
29 contractor, elevator inspector, or elevator mechanic.
30 (7) "Licensing program" means the program for licensing elevator
31 contractors, elevator inspectors, and elevator mechanics
32 established under this section and sections 7 through 16 of this
33 chapter.
34 (8) "Municipality" has the meaning set forth in IC 36-1-2-11.
35 (9) "Person" means:
36 (A) a natural person;
37 (B) the partners or members of a partnership or a limited
38 partnership;
39 (C) a state educational institution; or
40 (D) a corporation or the officers, directors, and employees of
41 the corporation.
42 (10) "Practitioner" means a person that holds:
EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

187
1 (A) an unlimited license;
2 (B) a limited or probationary license;
3 (C) a temporary license;
4 (D) an emergency license; or
5 (E) an inactive license.
6 (b) The commission and the department shall establish a program
7 to license elevator contractors, elevator mechanics, and elevator
8 inspectors.
9 (c) The department shall issue a license as an elevator contractor, an
10 elevator mechanic, or an elevator inspector to a person who qualifies
11 and complies with the provisions of the licensing program. A person
12 who receives a license under this chapter is subject to the supervision
13 and control of the department.
14 (d) The department may contract with public and private
15 institutions, agencies, businesses, and organizations to implement all
16 or part of its duties established under this chapter.
17 (e) The commission department may adopt rules under IC 4-22-2
18 to implement the licensing program.
