192
1 upgrade training programs.
2 For an individual's completion of a continuing education course to
3 satisfy the individual's continuing education requirement under this
4 chapter, the continuing education provider, instructor and the
5 curriculum must have been approved by the department.
6 (e) All instructors of continuing education courses must be approved
7 by the department. If an instructor is approved by the department, has
8 worked as an instructor teaching a curriculum approved by the
9 department at any time within the year preceding the expiration date of
10 the license, and submits proof of this work to the department, the
11 instructor is exempt from the requirements of subsection (c).
12 (f) Continuing education providers shall keep uniform records of
13 attendance at approved continuing education courses for at least ten
14 (10) years on forms designed and distributed by the department.
15 (g) A license holder who is unable to complete the continuing
16 education required under this chapter before the expiration of the
17 individual's license due to temporary physical or mental disability may
18 apply for a waiver from the department in accordance with the
19 following:
20 (1) A waiver application must be submitted to the department on
21 a form established by the department.
22 (2) A waiver application must be signed and accompanied by an
23 affidavit signed by the physician of the applicant attesting to the
24 applicant's temporary disability.
25 (h) After the cessation of the temporary disability, the applicant
26 must submit to the department a certification from the same physician,
27 if the physician is still the treating physician of the applicant, or from
28 a subsequent treating physician attesting to the termination of the
29 temporary disability.
30 (i) Upon the submission of the certification under subsection (h), the
31 department shall issue a temporary waiver of the continuing education
32 requirement. A temporary waiver is valid for ninety (90) days after the
33 date of issue and allows the individual to work as an elevator
34 contractor, elevator inspector, or elevator mechanic without the
35 completion of the continuing education requirement for ninety (90)
36 days.
37 (j) A temporary waiver of the continuing education requirement may
38 not be renewed.
