EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

203
1 chapter, the agency shall send a notice of the upcoming expiration of
2 a license or certificate to each holder of a license or certificate at least
3 ninety (90) days before the expiration of the license or certificate. The
4 notice must inform the holder of the license or certificate of the need
5 to renew the license or certificate and the requirement of payment of
6 the renewal fee. If this notice of expiration is not sent by the agency,
7 the holder of the license or certificate is not subject to a sanction for
8 failure to renew if, once notice is received from the agency, the license
9 or certificate is renewed within forty-five (45) days after receipt of the
10 notice.
11 (d) In administering an examination for licensure or certification,
12 the agency shall make the appropriate application forms available at
13 least thirty (30) days before the deadline for submitting an application
14 to all persons wishing to take the examination.
