17 (1) the applicant continues to meet the minimum requirements for
18 licensure or certification; and
19 (2) the applicant is not in violation of:
20 (A) the statute regulating the applicant's profession; or
21 (B) rules adopted by the board regulating the applicant's
22 profession.
23 (f) The agency shall process an application for renewal of a license
24 or certificate:
25 (1) not later than ten (10) days after the agency receives all
26 required forms and evidence; or
27 (2) within twenty-four (24) hours after the time that an applicant
28 for renewal appears in person at the agency with all required
29 forms and evidence.
30 This subsection does not require the agency to issue a renewal license
31 or certificate to an applicant if subsection (g) applies.
32 (g) The agency may delay issuing a license or certificate renewal for
33 up to one hundred twenty (120) days after the renewal date for the
34 purpose of permitting the board to investigate information received by
35 the agency that the applicant for renewal may have committed an act
36 for which the applicant may be disciplined. If the agency delays issuing
37 a license or certificate renewal, the agency shall notify the applicant
38 that the applicant is being investigated. Except as provided in
39 subsection (h), before the end of the one hundred twenty (120) day
40 period, the board shall do one (1) of the following:
41 (1) Deny the license or certificate renewal following a personal
42 appearance by the applicant before the board.
EH 1003—LS 6756/DI 92

204
1 (2) Issue the license or certificate renewal upon satisfaction of all
2 other conditions for renewal.
3 (3) Issue the license or certificate renewal and file a complaint
4 under IC 25-1-7.
5 (4) Upon agreement of the applicant and the board and following
6 a personal appearance by the applicant before the board, renew
7 the license or certificate and place the applicant on probation
8 status under IC 25-1-9-9.
9 (h) If an individual fails to appear before the board under subsection
10 (g), the board may take action on the applicant's license or certificate
11 allowed under subsection (g)(1), (g)(2), or (g)(3).
12 (i) The applicant's license or certificate remains valid until the final
13 determination of the board is rendered unless the renewal is denied or
14 the license is summarily suspended under IC 25-1-9-10.
15 (j) The license or certificate of the applicant for a license or
16 certificate renewal remains valid during the one hundred twenty (120)
17 day period unless the license or certificate renewal is denied following
18 a personal appearance by the applicant before the board before the end
19 of the one hundred twenty (120) day period. If the one hundred twenty
20 (120) day period expires without action by the board, the license or
21 certificate is automatically renewed at the end of the one hundred
22 twenty (120) day period.
23 (k) The board's renewal of a license or certificate does not preclude
24 the board from imposing sanctions on the licensee or certificate holder
25 as a result of a complaint filed by the attorney general after renewal of
26 the license or certificate.
27 (l) Notwithstanding any other statute or rule, the agency may stagger
28 license or certificate renewal cycles. However, if a renewal cycle for a
29 specific board or committee is changed, the agency must obtain the
30 approval of the affected board or committee.
31 (m) An application for a license, certificate, registration, or permit
32 is abandoned without an action of the board, if the applicant does not
33 complete the requirements to complete the application within one (1)
34 year after the date on which the application was filed. However, the
35 board may, for good cause shown, extend the validity of the application
36 for additional thirty (30) day periods. An application submitted after
37 the abandonment of an application is considered a new application.
