12 certified prelicensing courses of study provided by the person, the
13 percentage who passed the examination required by IC 27-1-15.6-5.
14 The commissioner shall determine only one (1) passing percentage
15 under this subsection for all lines of insurance described in
16 IC 27-1-15.6-7(a) for which the person provides classroom instruction
17 in certified prelicensing courses of study.
18 (g) The commissioner may, after notice and opportunity for a
19 hearing, do the following:
20 (1) Withdraw the certification of a course of study that does not
21 maintain reasonable standards, as determined by the
22 commissioner for the protection of the public.
23 (2) Disqualify a person that is currently qualified under
24 subsection (b) to render instruction in a certified prelicensing
25 course of study from rendering the instruction if the passing
26 percentage calculated under subsection (f) is less than forty-five
27 percent (45%).
28 (h) Current course materials for a prelicensing course of study that
29 is certified under this section must be submitted to the commissioner
30 upon request, but not less frequently than once every three (3) years.
