18 (13) Bond or coupon payments.
19 (14) Payroll costs.
20 (15) State, federal, or county taxes.
21 (16) Expenses that must be paid because of emergency
22 circumstances.
23 (17) Expenses incurred to advertise and promote the programs
24 and services of the library.
25 (18) Other expenses described in a library board resolution.
26 The library board shall review and allow the claim at the library board's
27 first regular or special meeting following the payment of a claim under
28 this section.
29 (c) Each payment of expenses lawfully incurred for library purposes
30 must be supported by a fully itemized invoice or other documentation.
31 The library director shall certify to the library board before payment
32 that each claim for payment is true and correct. The certification must
33 be on a form prescribed by the state board of accounts.
34 (d) Purchases of books, magazines, pamphlets, films, filmstrips,
35 microforms, microfilms, slides, transparencies, phonodiscs,
36 phonotapes, models, art reproductions, and all other forms of library
37 and audiovisual materials are exempt from the restrictions imposed by
38 IC 5-22.
39 (e) The purchase of library automation systems must meet the
40 standards established by the Indiana library and historical board under
41 IC 4-23-7.1-11(b).
