SECTION 99. IC 10-13-3-34 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY
1, 2027]. Sec. 34. (a) There is established a security and privacy
council that consists of nine (9) members selected under subsections
(b) and (c).
(b) The following six (6) members shall be appointed by and shall
serve at the pleasure of the governor:
(1) A prosecuting attorney.
(2) The police chief of a city.
(3) The sheriff of a county.
