"SECTION 23. IC 35-47.5-5-11, AS AMENDED BY P.L.158-2013,
SECTION 617, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS
[EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2027]: Sec. 11. A person who recklessly
violates a rule regarding the use of a regulated explosive adopted by the
commission department under IC 35-47.5-4-4.5 commits a Class A
misdemeanor. However, the offense is:
(1) a Level 6 felony if the violation of the rule proximately causes
bodily injury; and
(2) a Level 5 felony if the violation of the rule proximately causes
death.".
